main event: Four round, white objects were observed flying in formation over Love Field, Dallas, Texas on 1 August 1956.
interesting points: The objects were observed for a duration of six minutes,The formation consisted of one lead object and three following behind,The objects came from the Northeast, flew South, and then orbited before fading to the Northwest,Conclusions from the report suggested they were possibly aircraft, despite the unidentified nature of the sighting,The sighting occurred during the final approach for Love Field airport.
witness description: Registered nurse, X-ray technician, housewife, and student
